evitable. As a result, more government means less innovation. And the sectors that government owns are frozen in time.</p></div><div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-login" href="https://reason.com/wp-login.php?redirect_to=https%3A%2F%2Freason.com%2F2020%2F04%2F17%2Fthe-coronavirus-has-exposed-governmental-failures-it-might-also-offer-hope-for-change%2F">Log in to Reply <i class="fas fa-reply"></i></a></div></div></li><li class="comment byuser even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-8215606" data-sort-time="1587165457"><div id="div-comment-8215606" class="comment-body"><div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><div class="comment-author vcard"> <cite class="fn"><strong>JAQO</strong></cite></div> <a href="https://reason.com/2020/04/17/the-coronavirus-has-exposed-governmental-failures-it-might-also-offer-hope-for-change/#comment-8215606">April.17.2020 at 7:17 pm </a></div><div class="comment-content"><p>Are you serious Reason?</p></div><div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-login" href="https://reason.com/wp-login.php?redirect_to=https%3A%2F%2Freason.com%2F2020%2F04%2F17%2Fthe-coronavirus-has-exposed-governmental-failures-it-might-also-offer-hope-for-change%2F">Log in to Reply <i class="fas fa-reply"></i></a></div></div></li><li class="comment byuser odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-8215732" data-sort-time="1587171101"><div id="div-comment-8215732" class="comment-body"><div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><div class="comment-author vcard"> <cite class="fn"><strong>Robert Ore</strong></cite></div> <a href="https://reason.com/2020/04/17/the-coronavirus-has-exposed-governmental-failures-it-might-also-offer-hope-for-change/#comment-8215732">April.17.2020 at 8:51 pm </a></div><div class="comment-content"><p>Funny how the same folks lament the governments botched COVID response&#8230;</p><p>Want the same government overseeing their day-to-day health care needs under universal care.</p></div><div class="reply"><a re